deck: A crazed Spider-Fan is determined to win Spidey's heart, even through great lengths.
description:
Peter's lab partner, Christina, is a fan girl of Spidey's. She made a mind reading device for their project. However, the machine went awry and caused her to have hallucinations of Spider-Man. Persistent to win his heart, she will do anything just to get the man of his dreams, even by trying to eliminate Mary Jane from the picture.

Note 1: Max Dillon is presented here as a teenager instead of an adult.

Note 2: Also, Max is here without powers and only appeared in a cameo.
name: Head Over Heels

deck: Peter's classmate, a teenage Max Dillon, is out for revenge with a side of shock value.
description:
Max Dillon is a troubled young man. He was recently tormented by his classmates by tying him up with his eyes blindfolded. After a failed initiation to a fraternity, his mind finally snaps. A lighting soon hits the billboard that he hit with a brick, causing him the electrifying dynamo named, Electro. Electro will have his revenge after his experiences, but not if Spider-Man intervenes.

Note: The X-Men was referenced by Peter when he was thinking whether they attend parties or not. It was never clear if the series took place in the movie franchise or referring to it only.
name: The Party

deck: The mystery goes on and the continuation to Iron, Forged In fire: Part 1.
description: Tony Stark continues to investigate Obadiah Stane's possible involvement to Howard Stark's demise. Stane is now testing Tony's "Earth-Movers" to people who are willing to buy it. Meanwhile, the Mandarin makes his move while Tony suits up against Stane and his hay-wired Earth-Movers.
name: Iron, Forged In Fire: Part 2

deck: Flash Thompson's tutor is giving him a taste of intelligence and it's not going well.
description: Peter's high school bully, Flash Thompson has suddenly become more intellectual. As in, he is not dumb anymore. Flash says that he had help from his tutor named Dr. Zellner. But life is fading from Flash, quickly. Flash decides he has the perfect volunteer, Peter himself.
name: Flash Memory

deck: The Silver Sable targets Peter and his friends for a video tape.
description: It's Friday and Peter has plans with his friends. But during a press conference with the mayor of New York and a guest, someone is attempting to take the mayor's life. Luckily, Spider-Man was able to save them and was able to tape who was attempting to take down the mayor. When the assassin, Silver Sable, noticed she was recorded, she plans to kill Peter and his friends. However, she is not targeting the mayor. Who is she really targeting?
name: Spider-Man Dis-Sabled
Beyond the Valley of the Dinosaurs

deck: In the first episode of 'Son of Zorro', Jeff Stewart returns home from the Civil War. He learns from an old friend that corrupt politicians have taken advantage of the men being off at war to take control of the county. To put things right, Zorro rides again!
description: In the first episode of 'Son of Zorro', Jeff Stewart returns home from the Civil War. He learns from an old friend that corrupt politicians have taken advantage of the men being off at war to take control of the county. They've imposed severely high property taxes in order to seize lands and put a toll station on the only route in or out through the mountains to further line their pockets. With no legal recourse left to him, he dons the mask of Zorro at the urging of his ranch foreman Pancho.
name: Outlaw Country
